Se usan para posibilidad - autorizacion - permiso.... mas que todo
enfocado en permisos o autorizaciones.

may have / 	might have
may      /      might

may   --->  puede		             may have
might --->  pudo / podria                       might have


suject + may/might + v.base + complement    suject + may/might + have + v.pp + complement   

mario puede/podria/pudo estar mintiendo (hablamos de una posibilidad)
 - Mario might/may be lying yesterday.
 - Might mario be lying
 - Mario mayn't be lying.
-  May mario be lying?
 
 
 Ivan Puede/pudo/podria haber estado mintiendo
 - Ivan might have been lying.
 - might iva have been lying?
 - might not ivan have been lying?
 

podria haber ganado la loteria, pero no compre el boleto
i might have won the lottery, but i didn't buy the ticket.

puede que llueva mas tarde. Tomare una sombrilla
it may rain later. i will take an umbrella.


Lo intentaste, pero puede que no hayas sido constante.
you tried, but you mayn't have been  constant 
 

